WEBVTT

00:05.876 --> 00:08.943
Justice...

00:09.010 --> 00:10.376
what does that word mean ?

00:10.443 --> 00:13.710
Today, for example, it means
that when an individual

00:13.776 --> 00:15.977
is charged
with attempted murder,

00:16.043 --> 00:20.662
that charge must be proven
beyond any reasonable doubt.

00:20.662 --> 00:24.209
And in order to prove
attempted murder,

00:24.276 --> 00:27.576
only one thing matters : intent.

00:27.643 --> 00:28.910
Now, I'm not going
to lie to you.

00:28.977 --> 00:31.013
Gordie Brock screwed up
big time.

00:31.013 --> 00:34.777
He came home drunk,
he beat up his wife Deena

00:34.843 --> 00:36.447
and sent her to the hospital.

00:36.447 --> 00:41.309
But when Deena Brock was lying
on that floor unconscious,

00:41.376 --> 00:44.142
it was Gordie Brock who called
for an ambulance.

00:44.209 --> 00:48.576
It was Gordie Brock who stopped 
his wife from bleeding to death

00:48.643 --> 00:50.610
before help arrived.

00:50.676 --> 00:52.443
Does that make him a hero ?

00:52.509 --> 00:54.450
Obviously not,

00:54.476 --> 00:56.810
but it does clearly show
one thing :

00:56.877 --> 01:02.476
While he abused his wife,
he never meant to kill her.

01:02.543 --> 01:07.343
He... never... meant...
to kill her.

01:07.409 --> 01:11.077
You can hate Gordie Brock
if you want

01:11.142 --> 01:12.409
for beating his wife...

01:12.476 --> 01:13.910
I do...

01:13.977 --> 01:15.910
but when you go into that
jury room, 

01:15.977 --> 01:17.476
remember those six words

01:17.543 --> 01:20.409
because they go to the heart
of this case.

01:20.476 --> 01:22.610
See, you have a job,

01:22.676 --> 01:26.509
and your job
is to deliver justice.

01:26.576 --> 01:32.976
And thankfully, the prosecution
has made your job easy.

01:33.043 --> 01:34.876
Two words :

01:40.809 --> 01:42.909
Not guilty.

01:42.976 --> 01:44.410
Do they always
decide so fast ?

01:44.436 --> 01:46.310
Well, three hours
isn't my record for an acquittal,

01:46.376 --> 01:47.495
but it'll do.

01:47.545 --> 01:48.634
You really saved
my ass.

01:48.634 --> 01:50.347
You just remember
what we talked about.

01:50.347 --> 01:51.610
Got a meeting
tonight.

01:51.676 --> 01:52.810
Good, okay.

01:52.876 --> 01:54.510
You didn't just
save his life,

01:54.576 --> 01:56.610
you saved mine, too.

01:59.810 --> 02:01.576
WOMAN:
Shark strikes again.

02:01.643 --> 02:03.109
Oh, Madam
District Attorney.

02:03.176 --> 02:04.379
I should have tried
this one myself.

02:04.379 --> 02:05.727
You know, as much
as I love going

02:05.727 --> 02:07.193
head-to-head
with you, Jess,

02:07.193 --> 02:08.709
it wouldn't have
mattered this time.

02:08.709 --> 02:10.942
Attempted murder ?
Gordie Brock is headlines.

02:10.961 --> 02:12.376
You went for the
glory, you lost.

02:12.526 --> 02:13.625
I tried to put away
a wife beater.

02:13.692 --> 02:15.526
Gordie Brock
belongs in prison.

02:15.593 --> 02:17.159
Well, the jury
disagreed, didn't they ?

02:17.226 --> 02:18.593
But if it's
any consolation,

02:18.659 --> 02:20.693
you look really hot
in that suit.

02:20.760 --> 02:22.025
Dream on.
I will.

02:22.092 --> 02:24.059
MAN:
How you doing, Stark ?
Hey.

02:29.359 --> 02:34.860
* Oh, the shark, babe,
has such teeth, dear *

02:34.925 --> 02:39.259
* And he shows them 
pearly white *

02:39.326 --> 02:46.192
* Just a jackknife has old
MacHeath, dear *

02:46.259 --> 02:50.226
* And he keeps it, yeah,
out of sight... *

02:51.426 --> 02:54.226
Margaret, why be a buzz kill ?

02:56.000 --> 03:02.074
-= www.OpenSubtitles.org =-

03:18.373 --> 03:19.713
Suspect's in the kitchen.

03:28.753 --> 03:29.839
GORDIE:
It's my lawyer, boys.

03:30.339 --> 03:32.406
So why not save
everybody some time and money

03:32.473 --> 03:33.772
and let me go right now ?

03:48.039 --> 03:49.939
WOMAN:
It's a shame I canceled
the photo shoot.

03:50.006 --> 03:52.172
Margaret, why are you
still here ?

03:52.239 --> 03:54.839
I've been asking myself that
for nine long years.

03:54.905 --> 03:56.306
Well, then surely
you're familiar

03:56.373 --> 03:58.206
with the phrase
"cancel everything."

03:58.273 --> 03:59.673
Your clients are.

03:59.740 --> 04:01.072
You got to get back
on the horse.

04:01.139 --> 04:02.506
Now look, here's a tip, okay ?

04:02.573 --> 04:04.424
Why don't you take
the equestrian metaphors

04:04.424 --> 04:05.779
and shove 'em you know where ?

04:05.779 --> 04:06.839
Oh, that's nice.

04:06.905 --> 04:08.839
Why aren't you in school ?

04:08.905 --> 04:11.206
It's 4:30
in the afternoon, Dad.
Oh.

04:11.273 --> 04:13.430
Do you want
more green peppers in your eggs ?

04:13.450 --> 04:15.172
Not hungry.

04:15.239 --> 04:16.706
It's 'cause you're depressed.

04:16.772 --> 04:19.005
Hi.
Hi.

04:19.072 --> 04:20.736
Ooh, you smell.

04:20.736 --> 04:22.449
When was the last time
you took a shower ?

04:22.450 --> 04:24.039
Tuesday.

04:25.573 --> 04:27.239
Look, Dad, after
the whole Deena Brock thing,

04:27.306 --> 04:29.673
it makes perfect sense for you
to punish yourself out of guilt.

04:29.740 --> 04:31.789
The white teen Oprah speaks.

04:31.789 --> 04:33.763
Yes, well, the scars
of my broken home

04:33.763 --> 04:35.729
have made me wise
beyond my years.

04:35.729 --> 04:36.706
Come on, Dad,

04:36.772 --> 04:37.872
it's been a month.

04:37.939 --> 04:39.296
I'm really worried about you.

04:39.296 --> 04:41.586
These are good.

04:41.586 --> 04:42.912
I'm okay.
Yeah ?

04:42.912 --> 04:44.318
Really. Yes, I am.

04:43.972 --> 04:45.863
Shouldn't you
be getting home ?

04:45.863 --> 04:48.006
Oh, I just came by
to remind you about
the custody hearing.

04:48.072 --> 04:49.206
I don't do
custody, honey.

04:49.273 --> 04:51.172
Custody of <i>me,</i> Dad.

04:51.239 --> 04:52.506
I turned 16 last month ?

04:52.573 --> 04:53.673
Thanks for the card.

04:53.740 --> 04:55.206
Ouch. Sorry.

04:55.273 --> 04:57.872
Now I have to decide who gets
final custody, you or Mom.

04:57.939 --> 04:59.805
That judge was
a major putz.

04:59.872 --> 05:00.905
You got a phone call.

05:00.972 --> 05:02.673
I'm out.
It's the Mayor.

05:02.740 --> 05:04.206
Said something about
a ten-year audit

05:04.273 --> 05:05.905
on your city tax return.

05:06.172 --> 05:08.840
MAN:
 <i>Did you read Lopez</i>
 <i>this morning ?</i>

05:08.906 --> 05:10.872
No.
Aspen's still the playground
for the rich and famous

05:10.939 --> 05:13.328
but L.A.'s a new hot spot
to get away with murder.

05:13.328 --> 05:15.310
You should audit
his taxes.

05:15.310 --> 05:16.365
Truth is, I'm sick
of the poor going

05:16.365 --> 05:19.339
to jail for jaywalking
while millionaires 
kill each other

05:19.339 --> 05:20.905
without missing 
a massage.

05:20.972 --> 05:23.414
We're starting
a high profile crime unit

05:23.414 --> 05:24.255
in the DA's office

05:24.255 --> 05:26.206
to nail rich folk
with fancy lawyers like you.

05:27.504 --> 05:28.637
What's so funny ?

05:28.704 --> 05:30.337
I tell you what, Mr. Mayor.

05:30.404 --> 05:32.571
You put ten prosecutors
on a big-time case,

05:32.637 --> 05:34.671
you give 'em all
the money they can spend,

05:34.737 --> 05:36.871
and I'll bury 'em alive
every day of the week

05:36.938 --> 05:38.624
with a matinee on Wednesday
and another on Sunday.

05:38.624 --> 05:40.437
So you think
Devlin's incompetent ?

05:40.504 --> 05:42.204
Hey, she's got great legs,
but she doesn't know diddly

05:42.270 --> 05:43.671
about winning
big jury trials.

05:43.738 --> 05:44.839
That's why I'm bringing
somebody from the outside

05:44.839 --> 05:46.771
to head the unit.

05:46.838 --> 05:49.329
What schmo would
take that job ? Come on.

05:51.137 --> 05:54.204
Me a prosecutor ? No.

05:54.270 --> 05:55.371
Come on. 
Why not, huh ?

05:56.456 --> 05:58.057
I eat prosecutors
for breakfast.

05:58.057 --> 05:59.823
They're my main source
of fiber. Come on.

05:59.890 --> 06:01.356
Who better to shake up
the DA's unit ? Huh ?

06:01.423 --> 06:03.889
Winning is what you do
and it's what makes you the man.

06:03.956 --> 06:05.490
And I'd consider
this a personal favor.

06:05.556 --> 06:07.156
Jessica would
never go for it.

06:07.223 --> 06:09.790
I've got a 67%
approval rating.

06:09.857 --> 06:11.857
She's got editorials
screaming for her head.

06:11.922 --> 06:13.123
She'll do what I say.

06:13.189 --> 06:15.634
Manny, give me
one good reason

06:15.634 --> 06:17.256
I should even
consider this.

06:17.834 --> 06:18.761
I'll give you
three, <i>hermano.</i>

06:18.761 --> 06:21.167
You feel bad
about Deena Brock,

06:20.228 --> 06:22.893
you're sick of playing
on the wrong side,

06:22.893 --> 06:25.195
 ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ? ?

06:41.460 --> 06:48.460
<font color="#ffff00">www.1000fr.com present</font>

06:52.936 --> 06:59.936
<font color="#ffff00">sync:FRM@gadence</font>

07:03.234 --> 07:04.703
Sir, she's on the phone.

07:04.703 --> 07:07.031
Really ? Come on.

07:07.031 --> 07:08.260
Let's get this over with.

07:08.260 --> 07:10.635
Let me call you back.

07:10.702 --> 07:12.934
Welcome to the District
Attorney's office, Mr. Stark.

07:13.001 --> 07:14.568
Ms. Devlin.

07:14.635 --> 07:16.702
Well, this baby should get me
out of a few speeding tickets.

07:17.802 --> 07:19.967
Thank you.
Thank you.

07:20.574 --> 07:22.474
Do you mind telling me
what the hell you're up to ?

07:22.540 --> 07:23.707
Wow, look at these digs, huh ?

07:23.774 --> 07:24.941
Pretty good for a city employee.

07:25.006 --> 07:26.407
Comes with a great
parking spot, too.

07:26.474 --> 07:28.752
Unfortunately, some jerk
has parked in it.

07:28.752 --> 07:30.600
Wow, some people have
no respect, do they ?

07:30.600 --> 07:33.214
Hmm, look at that.
Terrible.

07:33.214 --> 07:34.784
So, what, you think you can
just waltz in here

07:34.784 --> 07:36.651
and cleanse your conscience
by putting away a few felons ?

07:36.718 --> 07:37.651
Hey, the Mayor asked for me.

07:37.718 --> 07:39.051
You know what I want, Jess ?

07:39.118 --> 07:40.418
I want us just to all be able
to get along.

07:40.484 --> 07:42.185
And I want the Rams
to come back to L.A.,

07:42.251 --> 07:44.085
but you know what ?
Not holding my breath.

07:44.151 --> 07:46.352
You know, I made my bones
humiliating this office

07:46.418 --> 07:47.718
on a daily basis

07:47.784 --> 07:49.517
but I want you to know
it was never personal.

07:49.584 --> 07:52.076
That's because for you,
the legal system's just a game

07:52.076 --> 07:53.051
to be played for fun
and profit.

07:53.118 --> 07:54.955
Do you mind ?
You know what ?
You make that sound

07:54.955 --> 07:57.420
like a bad thing.
Maybe not for a defense lawyer,

07:57.420 --> 07:59.151
but a Deputy DA represents
this city.

07:59.218 --> 08:00.664
And generally
not very well.

08:00.664 --> 08:02.227
You are a good attorney,

08:02.227 --> 08:03.919
but the people
in yr office, they...

08:03.919 --> 08:05.051
I don't know. What's the
word I'm looking for ?

08:05.118 --> 08:06.718
Oh, yeah, suck.

08:06.784 --> 08:08.118
Big trials require
a big gun.

08:08.185 --> 08:09.551
Oh, please,
you screwed up.

08:09.617 --> 08:10.718
We both know
that's why you're here.

08:10.784 --> 08:12.051
Oh.

08:12.118 --> 08:13.606
No matter how many criminals
you put away,

08:13.606 --> 08:15.551
Deena Brock's blood's
still going to be on your hands.

08:15.617 --> 08:16.851
Yeah, what about your hands,
Jess ?

08:16.918 --> 08:18.452
If this office
had the faintest clue how

08:18.517 --> 08:19.520
to mount an effective
prosecution,

08:19.520 --> 08:21.884
the guy'd still be in jail
and she'd still be alive.

08:21.951 --> 08:24.851
Well, this should be fun.

08:24.918 --> 08:27.018
Yeah. Mardi Gras.

08:27.085 --> 08:29.308
 <i>County of L.A. v.</i>
 <i>Jennifer Dennison.</i>

08:29.308 --> 08:30.352
Are you joking ?
That's a dog. Woof.

08:30.418 --> 08:31.551
Accused is a
20-year-old singer...

08:31.617 --> 08:32.664
Yeah, charged
with second-degree murder

08:32.664 --> 08:34.553
in the death of Terrence Rourke
at the Chateau Hotel.

08:34.553 --> 08:36.150
Accused claims
the victim raped her

08:36.160 --> 08:37.484
and she stabbed him
in self-defense.

08:37.551 --> 08:38.751
Am I supposed
to be impressed ?

08:38.818 --> 08:39.751
Guilty as sin,
you're right,

08:39.818 --> 08:41.150
but unwinnable.
Next.

08:41.217 --> 08:42.792
All right,
you listen to me.

08:42.792 --> 08:45.114
Delgado may have
forced me to hire you,

08:45.114 --> 08:46.953
but this is
my office.

08:46.953 --> 08:49.385
You prosecute
the cases I choose.

08:49.452 --> 08:50.452
Okay.

08:52.884 --> 08:54.751
What, the morgue
wasn't available ?

08:58.118 --> 09:00.118
Break a leg, Counselor.

09:00.185 --> 09:01.918
I hear he bribes jurors.

09:01.985 --> 09:03.751
Zero conscience.
He's scum.

09:03.818 --> 09:05.185
He won the Frye case

09:05.251 --> 09:07.185
by getting Judge Kranepool's
kid into Berkeley.

09:07.251 --> 09:08.651
That's completely
unethical.

09:08.718 --> 09:10.251
And the conviction rate
of this office

09:10.318 --> 09:11.484
is completely pathetic.

09:11.551 --> 09:13.551
And it was Harvard,
by the way.

09:13.617 --> 09:16.484
Well, it's clear you think
you know me,

09:16.551 --> 09:18.418
let's see what
I know about you.

09:18.484 --> 09:21.484
Richard "Casey" Woodland,
backup QB, USC.

09:21.551 --> 09:23.818
Dad's a state senator,
charming, good with a jury,

09:23.884 --> 09:25.951
weak on the facts,
not a rocket scientist.

09:26.018 --> 09:28.684
Billie Willis, smart,
passionate,

09:28.751 --> 09:30.718
lets emotion
cloud her judgment.

09:30.784 --> 09:31.918
Martin Alende...

09:31.985 --> 09:32.951
 <i>Allende.</i>

09:33.018 --> 09:34.118
 <i>Loyola Law Review.</i>

09:34.185 --> 09:35.452
Great on paper,
weak on his feet.

09:35.517 --> 09:37.285
Couldn't close a window.
And of course...

09:37.352 --> 09:38.385
Take your best shot.

09:38.452 --> 09:39.918
Raina Troy, tough, brilliant,

09:39.985 --> 09:41.951
and I used to <i>dream</i>
of getting you on a case.

09:42.018 --> 09:43.551
Major authority problem.

09:43.617 --> 09:45.118
A contempt citation
waiting to happen.

09:45.185 --> 09:46.100
Whatever.

09:46.100 --> 09:47.660
I rest my case.

09:47.660 --> 09:51.118
I have a dossier on every single
prosecutor in this building.

09:51.185 --> 09:52.838
Know thy enemy.

09:52.838 --> 09:53.651
Aren't we on
the same side now ?

09:53.718 --> 09:55.285
No, the jury's out,
isn't it ?

09:55.352 --> 09:56.985
But of course,
if the dragon lady
assigned you to me,

09:57.051 --> 09:58.352
I guess you're
on her hit list.

09:58.418 --> 09:59.553
That means you're 
damaged goods

09:59.553 --> 10:01.651
and that means that
we have something
in common.

10:01.718 --> 10:04.276
Madeleine Poe.
You're not on the list.

10:04.276 --> 10:05.051
I volunteered for the unit.

10:05.118 --> 10:06.684
Well, I appreciate that,
but you're not on the list.

10:06.751 --> 10:09.218
I graduated cum laude
from Stanford Law,

10:09.285 --> 10:10.684
clerked for the Ninth Circuit,

10:10.751 --> 10:12.584
and I've lead this office
in convictions

10:12.651 --> 10:13.884
for the last two years.

10:13.951 --> 10:15.985
I intend to become
a defense attorney,

10:16.051 --> 10:17.418
and I'm here to learn
from the best.

10:17.484 --> 10:18.651
Well, there you go,
sucking up...

10:18.718 --> 10:20.661
an effective
tactic. Sit.

10:20.661 --> 10:22.018
Thank you.
You know, people say that

10:22.085 --> 10:24.884
"high-priced defense attorneys"
beat prosecutors because

10:24.951 --> 10:27.851
it's easier to prove reasonable
doubt than certain guilt.

10:27.918 --> 10:31.251
But there's a simple explanation
for why I always win

10:31.318 --> 10:33.517
and you always lose...

10:33.584 --> 10:36.751
my vastly superior abilities
as a lawyer notwithstanding.

10:36.818 --> 10:39.584
A prosecutor
must conform his case

10:39.651 --> 10:41.784
to the demands
of the legal system.

10:41.851 --> 10:45.584
A defense attorney
conforms the legal system

10:45.651 --> 10:47.517
to the demands of his case.

10:47.584 --> 10:49.751
You want to win ?
Grab a pencil.

10:49.818 --> 10:52.185
I live by three simple rules...

10:52.251 --> 10:54.418
my cutthroat manifesto.

10:54.484 --> 10:58.751
These rules guide every single
decision I make

10:58.818 --> 11:00.651
on every single case.

11:00.718 --> 11:03.985
Rule number one : Trial is war,
second place is death.

11:04.051 --> 11:07.617
Rule number two:
Truth is relative.

11:07.684 --> 11:09.051
Pick one that works.

11:09.118 --> 11:11.018
Rule number three:

11:11.085 --> 11:14.452
In a jury trial, there are only
12 opinions that matter,

11:14.517 --> 11:18.517
and...Ms. Troy...yours most
decidedly is not one of them.

11:18.584 --> 11:20.285
Now from this day forward,

11:20.352 --> 11:22.985
every case will be
David versus Goliath.

11:23.051 --> 11:24.251
And guess who's
holding the slingshot ?

11:24.318 --> 11:26.951
Now, I have some bad news,

11:27.018 --> 11:28.617
and I have some truly
horrible news.

11:28.684 --> 11:30.985
The bad news is from one of
your lamer colleagues

11:31.051 --> 11:33.318
we have inherited
the Dennison case.

11:33.385 --> 11:34.784
The jury is lousy,

11:34.851 --> 11:37.285
the opposition has unlimited
resources.

11:37.352 --> 11:39.185
The truly horrible news...

11:39.251 --> 11:42.617
we go to trial in 48 hours.

11:42.684 --> 11:45.185
For this to work,
you must accept

11:45.251 --> 11:48.251
that winning is the only thing
that matters.

11:48.318 --> 11:49.418
What about justice ?
Hey.

11:49.484 --> 11:51.118
Your job is to win.

11:51.185 --> 11:53.185
Justice is God's problem.

11:53.251 --> 11:57.918
So, guys, you're either on
the bus or you're off the bus.

11:57.985 --> 11:59.218
Let's get to work.

11:59.285 --> 12:00.918
I've seen you on television.

12:00.985 --> 12:02.251
Occupational hazard.

12:02.318 --> 12:04.051
You represent criminals.

12:04.118 --> 12:05.418
Terry wasn't a criminal.

12:05.484 --> 12:06.684
Mrs. Rourke...

12:06.751 --> 12:07.884
I'm here to help you,

12:07.951 --> 12:09.452
so please tell me
about your son.

12:09.517 --> 12:12.218
Terry was a great kid.

12:12.285 --> 12:15.517
He always loved music
and photography.

12:15.584 --> 12:17.318
Shooting videos,
he could do both.

12:17.385 --> 12:20.251
Did Terry have
an active social life ?

12:20.318 --> 12:22.484
He dated a lot.

12:22.551 --> 12:23.751
Girls liked him.

12:23.818 --> 12:26.151
I have to ask.

12:26.218 --> 12:28.452
Was he in the habit of
having one-night stands ?

12:30.751 --> 12:32.452
Do you have children, Mr. Stark ?

12:32.517 --> 12:35.085
A 16-year-old daughter.

12:35.151 --> 12:37.884
Then you know once they
start to grow up,

12:37.951 --> 12:39.784
they don't always tell you
everything.

12:39.851 --> 12:41.851
Maybe you don't want to know.

12:41.918 --> 12:43.251
Just pray they're safe.

12:44.918 --> 12:47.484
I believe this girl murdered
your son.

12:47.551 --> 12:49.018
